<p>Factor both the numerator and the denominator,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\lim_{x \to 1} \br{ \frac{x^2-1}{x^2+3x-4} } 
		&amp;=  \lim_{x \to 1} { \left[ \frac{ \cancel{(x-1)}(x+1)}{ \cancel{(x-1)}(x+4)} \right] }  \\
		&amp;= \lim_{x \to 1} \br{ \frac{x+1}{x+4} }  \\
		&amp;= \frac{1+1}{1+4} \\
		&amp;= \frac{2}{5}		\tagans
\end{align*}\]

